Braavo Capital raises $70m venture funding
New York based mobile financing firm Braavo Capital has secured $70m in venture funding from Mark 2 Capital. Braavo uses data, integrations and automation to deliver performance-based funding that's customized for mobile growth.
Braavo Capital said it raised debt and equity financing of more than $70 million dollars in a deal led by existing investor Mark 2 Capital and joined by angel investors and family offices.
The money will be used to grow the company’s financing originations and support its growth.
— dbray Media (@dbrayMedia) 
